&lt;p&gt;Are you looking for a new challenge and to find a fulfilling career in healthcare? Do you want to make a difference to people’s lives?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;South Tees Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust provides acute and community services across Teesside and North Yorkshire to over 1.5 million people. As an integrated provider we currently have opportunities available in acute care, primary care hospitals and community services. Do you know that we run services in East Cleveland, North Yorkshire and Hambleton and Richmondshire?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A passion for delivering high quality patient care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Outstanding communication and interpersonal skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to deliver safe, effective and compassionate care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A commitment to continual personal and professional development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you do then come and be a part of the team at our high performing trust, which prides itself on excellence and aims to set the national standard for excellence in patient safety, quality and continuous improvement. Our 9,000 staff have an important role in fulfilling this aim, making working for the trust very rewarding. Staff have access to a range of benefits including pension, salary sacrifice schemes, on-site nursery and staff experience initiatives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have specific jobs advertised but these may not be in the area you are currently interested in applying so this advert is for you. Please apply stating your preferred area of practice and location and let us see if we can match you to a job.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like more details, please contact us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Eileen Aylott (Assistant Director of Nursing Education and Workforce)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Email: eileen.aylott@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tel: 01642 850850, ext. 52311&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
